<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-27-0561 </DOCNO><TEXT>Sweden, like many other countries, had to search for alternative energysources after the oil crisis of the seventies. Even as late as 1979,petroleum had nearly a 70% share in power supply; today, this share hasdecreased to 45%. Sweden is the world's first country to decide on anuclear phase-out. Considerable efforts will be required to substituteboth nuclear power and petroleum. Electric power generation, for example,is based on nuclear energy and hydropower in equal shares. In early 1988,the Social Democrat Government presented a programme for nuclear phase-outafter the mid-nineties.</TEXT></DOC>